notesStmt.note: Title from caption title (f. 1r); date based on latest date in manuscript (f. 42r).

msContents.summary: Satirical songs about politics and women from the 17th and early 18th centuries, including songs by Blot, Benserade, Boussy-Rabutin, and Coulanges, with musical notation, annotations, and corrections. The last item in the volume is a satirical version of Antoine Houdar La Motte's verse tragedy, Inees de Castro, "parodiée en mirliton" (f. 170-180).

supportDesc.extent: 182 leaves : 370 x 226 (280 x 121) mm. bound to 379 x 250 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 182 + i (contemporary paper); 1, 3-62, 64, 64-172, 163-164, 175-[182]; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Frame ruled with an additional column for annotations between the main writing area and the gutter on each page.

decoDesc.decoNote: Ink drawing of a fish or whale (f. 160r).

binding.p: Contemporary marbled calf with the arms of Bonnier de la Mosson on the upper cover and his name on the lower cover (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Bonnier de la Mosson (Joseph Bonnier, baron of Mossoni, gilt-tooled arms, upper cover; gilt-tooled name, lower cover).
Formerly owned by Viollet le Duc (bookplate, inside upper cover).
